	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64565969"><p>The 10-1 against was because of insufficient science studying it, which the US doesn't allow (headslap).</p><p>MDMA, LSD, and even Methamphetamine were successfully used as "shell shock" (now known as PTSD) treatment before the drug schedules even existed. Since Nixon created it, the DEA gets the final vote for what schedule any drug gets put on, and tend to put so-called party drugs on schedule 1 (no medical use and high chance of abuse). Even the DEA court said cannabis shouldn't be on schedule 1 and should be schedule 3 and the DEA itself blocked their own court's ruling.</p><p>How the **** can you study a drug's effectiveness against something like PTSD when it is a felony for researchers to even possess it? So yeah, I agree with the researchers, but the real villain is the DEA, which ****ing bans any research.</p></div>
	</div>

